{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17631380","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17631380"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:26:27+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:26:27+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17370"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17370","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17370"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10060"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70374"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10060","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10060"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17370"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55838"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5334"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23553"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23629"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70374","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70374"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ECultural competence is essential for healthcare providers to deliver effective care to diverse populations.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes a key principle of cultural competence in healthcare?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Recognising and respecting diverse cultural perspectives in healthcare delivery","Expecting all patients to adapt to the dominant healthcare culture","Focusing exclusively on language barriers in cross-cultural care","Requiring healthcare providers to become experts in all cultures","Treating all patients identically regardless of cultural background"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is that cultural competence involves \u003Cstrong\u003Erecognising and respecting diverse cultural perspectives in healthcare delivery\u003C/strong\u003E. This principle acknowledges that different cultural groups may have varying beliefs, values, and practices regarding health and illness that need to be understood and respected to provide effective care.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExpecting all patients to adapt to the dominant healthcare culture\u003C/strong\u003E demonstrates a lack of cultural sensitivity and creates barriers to accessing healthcare.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFocusing exclusively on language barriers in cross-cultural care\u003C/strong\u003E fails to address the broader aspects of cultural competence including beliefs, values, and practices.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERequiring healthcare providers to become experts in all cultures\u003C/strong\u003E sets an unrealistic expectation when the focus should be on developing general cultural awareness and sensitivity.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETreating all patients identically regardless of cultural background\u003C/strong\u003E ignores the importance of individualised care that considers cultural factors affecting health beliefs and behaviours.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECultural competence requires ongoing development of awareness, knowledge, and skills to work effectively with people from different cultural backgrounds. It involves understanding how cultural factors influence health beliefs, behaviours, and outcomes.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Cultural competence involves understanding and respecting different cultural beliefs, values, and practices in healthcare delivery.","The four key components of cultural competence are awareness, knowledge, skills, and encounters.","Cultural safety focuses on addressing power imbalances and ensuring healthcare is delivered in ways that do not diminish cultural identity."],"references":["Stubbe DE. Practicing Cultural Competence and Cultural Humility in the Care of Diverse Patients. Focus (Am Psychiatr Publ). 2020 Jan;18(1):49-51. doi: 10.1176/appi.focus.20190041. Epub 2020 Jan 24. PMID: 32047398; PMCID: PMC7011228."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55838"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17370"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55838","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/55838"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-14T20:06:45+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-14T20:07:51+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10060"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70374"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","positio